        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Myrtos Beach</h2>
        <p>Around the northern tip of Kefalonia you'll find the beautiful <strong>Mytros Beach</strong> with its brilliant light blue waters below the cliffs. You can also walk under the Myrtos Cave on the shoreline, and take in amazing views of the beach and coastline from high above at the <strong>Myrtos Beach Viewpoint</strong> pull-offs on the northern and southern side of the beach.</p>
    </section>


    <!-- Assos, Greece Dropdown -->
    <section class="destination-section">
        <a class="anchor" id="assos"></a>
        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Assos, Greece</h2>
        <p>You might also visit the lovely nearby village of <strong>Assos</strong>, which features small beaches and the possibility of taking in views over the village, by hiking up the peninsula hill that connects to the town. Atop the hill you'll find the ruins of the <strong>Venetian Castle</strong> you can explore. From the top of the peninsula you're rewarded with excellent views over the coasts.</p>
        <p>The hike to reach the entrance of the Venetian Castle is approximately 0.8 miles (1.3 km) one way from Assos.</p>
    </section>



