        <p>On the western side of the Kefalonia you'll find another popular scenic beach with clear vibrant blue waters, <strong>Petani Beach</strong>. This stunning beach sits below giant cliffs which stretch out into the ocean making for exceptional scenery.</p>
    </section>


    <!-- Sami, Greece Dropdown -->
    <section class="destination-section">
        <a class="anchor" id="sami"></a>
        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Sami, Greece</h2>
        <p>Near the island's central port town of Sami you'll find an incredible and unique attraction, the <strong>Melissani Lake Cave</strong>. This stunning cave is open from above and contains magnificent deep blue waters that you can enjoy with a short boat ride tour.</p>
        <p>Nearby the cave you might visit the beautiful <strong>Antisamos Beach</strong> with its clear waters and views  out to Ithaca Island.</p>
    </section>


    <!-- Mount Ainos Dropdown -->
    <section class="destination-section">
        <a class="anchor" id="mount-ainos"></a>
        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Mount Ainos</h2>
        <p>One of the highest peaks of all the Ionian Islands is <strong>Mount Ainos</strong>, which offers breathtaking panoramic views from the top.</p>
        <p>The trailhead for Mount Ainos begins at a radio broadcasting station at the end of the road near the top, where you can walk along a 4.1 mile (6.6 km) round-trip loop trail featuring various viewpoints overlooking the island and coast. You'll also be walking through peaceful forests along this hike.</p>
    </section>




